message.entry: In block ''{0}'', when the ''Array layout'' Configuration parameter is set to 'Row-major' and ''Interpolation Order'' parameter is set 'Column-major', or vice versa, code generation is not supported when the table size is tunable and the Number of sub-table selection dimensions is set to a value greater than 0.
When the Prelookup and the Interpolation Using Prelookup blocks are used together, the index output of the ''{0}'' block must feed the index input of the ''{1}'' block.
When the Prelookup and the Interpolation Using Prelookup blocks are used together, the fraction output of the ''{0}'' block must feed the fraction input of the ''{1}'' block.
Half-precision data type is not supported for ''{0}'' table data.
